<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="GAL" stage="Rev" version="B">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:50:39Z" when="2009-10-02 03:50:39Z" stage="Draft">initial draft by Pdt. Max Jacob (almarhum); C&amp;B Grimes, team advisors; this book, B. Grimes; ?? is point for initial comparison, if there are questions re: exegesis; other resources: Hawaii CE; GNT; exegetical team check in Darwin, Aug. 2004 with Mus and June; Read through + revisions with Chuck &amp; team, Aug 04; UNS checked by Mus in Kupang, Sept 2004 (details below); BT by Barbara; consultant checked by Marge Crofts in Kupang, 7 October 2004; reviewed by Chuck at team's request to ensure all the codes and info are in the right places; read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:54:55Z" when="2014-02-24 10:54:55Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 7 October 2004 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Transl Cons ReporKMepis.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-19 01:45:27Z" when="2015-01-19 01:45:27Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read thru for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina at UBB. BT cleaned up a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Galatia</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi jama'at dong di<bt>to the congregations at</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Galatia<bt>Galatia</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus buka dia pung surat<bt>Paulus opens his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Salam dari beta, Paulus. Beta kirim ini surat kasi sodara orang parcaya dong yang ada di jama'at-jama'at di propinsi Galatia. Sodara-sodara yang ada sama-sama deng beta di sini, ada titip salam kasi sang bosong ju.<bt>Greetings from me, Paulus. I send this letter to the believer siblings who are in the congregations in Galatia province. The siblings who are together with me here also, are sending greetings to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta kasi inga sang bosong bilang, Allah Bapa deng Yesus Kristus yang utus sang beta, bukan manusia. Yesus Kristus tu, andia Orang yang Tuhan su kirim datang. Kristus mati, ma Tuhan kasi idop kambali. Ais Dong tu, yang suru sang beta ko pi kasi tau orang-orang so'al Kabar Bae.<bt>I remind you that it was Allah Father and Yesus Kristus are who commissioned me, [it's] not humans. That Yesus Kristus, that's the Person whom God2 has already sent. Kristus died, but God2 made [him] live again. Then They are the ones who ordered me to go tell people about this Good News. [NOTE: TBT article on explicating meaning of “Christ”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle, not from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle, not from man, neither through man, but through Jesus Christ, and God the Father who raised him from the dead, and all the brothers who are with me, to the congregations in Galatia;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Beta sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, andia kotong pung Bapa, deng Yesus Kristus, andia kotong pung Bos. Beta minta ko Dong kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I pray to God our Father, and Yesus Kristus our Boss. I ask that They show Their good liver's to you-pl (*key term mercy) so that you can live in safety/security, (relational) peace, and (inner) peace. [NOTE to daughter translations: 3 aspects of Gk /eirene/. This should be the same phrasing you used in 5T's and James. E.g. 2 Thes 1:2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xaris: favor, grace, gift eirene: well-being,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">xaris: favor, grace, gift eirene: well-being, welfare, health, peace<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta minta ko Dong kasi tunju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Beta minta ko Dong kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae sang bosong ko bosong bisa idop badame.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kristus mati ko hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala dong, deng kasi bebas kotong dari jahat yang ada di ini dunya sakarang. Itu samua iko Allah Bapa pung mau.<bt>Kristus died to erase away our-inc wrongs, and to free us-inc from the evil that is in this world now. All of that, is according to Allah Father's will. [NOTE to daughter translations: Check that “all that” doesn't refer to “evil in this world” but to Christ's sacrifice. ALT: “All of that that Kristus did, is according to Father God's will.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exairew: rescue, set free, deliver aiwn:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">exairew: rescue, set free, deliver aiwn: age, period of time<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: who gave himself for our sins, to deliver us from the present evil age, according to the will of God, our Father,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dari dunya pung jahat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">dari dunya pung jahat</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Andia ko kotong musti puji-puji tarús sang Dia! Batúl tu!<bt>That's why we must continually praise Him! That's true! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksa: glory, praise. LITERALLY: to whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">doksa: glory, praise. LITERALLY: to whom is glory forever and ever, Amen.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus mara tagal orang Galatia su bale balakang dari ajaran yang batúl<bt>Paulus is angry because the Galatia people have turned their backs on the true teaching</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sodara dong! Beta sonde bisa mangarti lai sang bosong! Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang bosong, tagal Dia mau ko bosong kanál Dia pung hati bae. Ma akurang ko bosong bale balakang capát-capát ko pi parcaya deng ajaran laen<bt>Siblings! I can no longer understand you-pl (+frustration)! God has chosen you, because He wants you you to know His good liver. But why have you quickly turned your backs to go believe in a different teaching</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thaumazw: wonder, marvel, be amazed, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">thaumazw: wonder, marvel, be amazed, be surprised, be astonished metatithemi: change, be removed, desert, turn away from, transfer<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: I am amazed that you so quickly are changing from the one who called you into the grace of Christ to another "good news,"</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />yang sonde batúl? Dolu beta su ajar yang batúl so'al Yesus Kristus pung Kabar Bae. Ma sakarang tukang tipu dong su datang ko putar-balek itu Kabar Bae, sampe bekin bingung sang bosong.<bt>that is not true? Previously I had taught that which is true about Yesus Kristus' Good News. But now habitual decievers have come and twisted that Good News, to.the.point.of making you confused.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, trouble,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, trouble, upset, confuse metastrephw: change, alter, pervert<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: which is not another [good news]. But there are some who are stirring you up, and want to pervert the Good News of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ati-ati! Nanti Tuhan kutuk itu orang yang datang ajar Kabar Bae yang sonde sama ke yang dolu botong su ajar tu. Biar itu orang dari botong, ko, Tuhan pung ana bua satu dari sorga ko, dia pasti kaná kutuk!<bt>Be careful! Later God2 will curse that person/s who comes teaching Good News which is not the same as that which we-exc previously taught. Even if that person is one of you, or, God2's underling from heaven (*angel) or [whoever], he will surely be affected by a curse! [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. here is “let him be accursed”; but in KM “biar ko” clashes with use of “biar” at beginning of sentence. ALT1: copy end of vs.9; ALT2 (as in CEV): “I pray/hope God will punish”. Dhao has a ‘curse’ word that collocates with humans as agent, but not with God as agent, so be careful. This problem is also noted in TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anathema: accursed, cursed, damned, condemned to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anathema: accursed, cursed, damned, condemned to Hell, set apart for destruction LITERALLY: But even if we or an angel from Heaven preach another "good news" to you, different from what we preached, let him be cursed.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Botong su kasi tau ini hal memang dari dolu. Ma sakarang beta mau kasi inga ulang lai, bagini: kalo ada orang yang datang ajar laen dari itu Kabar Bae yang dolu bosong su tarima tu, biar Tuhan ju kutuk ame sang dia.<bt>We-exc have really already told these thing from before. But now I want to remind [you] again, like this: if there is a person who come teaching different from that Good News which previously you accepted, may God2 also curse [+accomplishment] him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As we have said before,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As we have said before, so I say again, if anyone preaches another "good news'" to you, different from what you received, let him be cursed.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Beta barani omong bagitu, tagal beta mau bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati, bukan manusia pung hati. Bosong pikir beta ada mau cari-cari muka di manusia, ko? Sonde! Te kalo beta bekin bagitu, na, beta sonde pantas jadi Kristus pung orang suru-suru.<bt>I dare to speak like that, because I want to make God2's liver happy, not human's liver. Do you think I want to seek face (=please) among humans, [+tag question]? No! Cuz if I did like that, na, I would not be appropriate/worthy to be Kristus' slave/servant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Am I now looking for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Am I now looking for people's approval or God's? Or do I try to please people? If people's approval, then I would no longer be a servant [slave] of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus carita ulang karmana dia jadi Tuhan Yesus pung utusan<bt>Paulus retells how he came to be the Lord Yesus' envoy (*apostle)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** changed to avoid impression of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** changed to avoid impression of question</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sodara dong! Beta mau kasi tau tarús taráng bilang, itu Kabar Bae yang beta ajar sang bosong tu, bukan manusia yang karang-karang.<bt>Siblings! I want to tell [you] very explicitly/clearly that, that Good News which I taught to you, it's not humans who created it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I want you to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I want you to know, brothers, the Good News which I preached is not according to people;</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta sonde tarima dari manusia, deng sonde ada manusia yang ajar sang beta. Te Yesus Kristus sandiri yang buka kasi tau dia pung arti sang beta.<bt>I did not receive [it] from humans, and it's not humans who taught it to me. Cuz it's Yesus Kristus himself who opened/revealed &amp; told [SVC] it's meaning to me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Neither did I receive it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Neither did I receive it from people, nor was I taught it, but by revelation of Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tantu bosong su dengar carita so'al beta pung idop dolu, waktu beta masi pegang agama Yahudi, aa? Itu waktu, beta siksa satenga mati sang Tuhan pung orang, ko mau kasi ancor buang sang dong.<bt>Surely you have heard the story about my former life when I still held on to the Yahudi religion, right? At that time, I mistreated very badly God2's people in order to completely destroy them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="porthew: destroy, annihilate, make havoc of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">porthew: destroy, annihilate, make havoc of, ravage, waste LITERALLY: For you heard of my past way of life in the Jewish religion, that I persecuted the church of God excessively, and destroyed it.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:3, 22:4-5, 26:9-11</note><v n="14" />Deng itu waktu ju, beta hati manyala ko balajar so'al agama Yahudi, lebe dari orang Yahudi laen yang sama umur deng beta. Deng beta ni, yang paling rajin kasi jalan botong pung nene-moyang dong pung adat deng atoran agama samua.<bt>And at that time also, my liver shone/flared (=was enthusiastic/zealous) to study about Yahudi religion, more than other Yahudi people who were the same age as me. And I here, [am the one] who was extremely diligent in carrying out all our-ex ancestors' traditions and religious regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati manyala = enthusiastic, zealous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">hati manyala = enthusiastic, zealous</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prokoptw: go forward, go ahead, advance,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">prokoptw: go forward, go ahead, advance, excel sunelikiwtes: contemporary, same age group<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>zelotes: enthusiast, burn out for something, zealot, to do and defend something paradosis: tradition, custom<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: and I went ahead in the Jewish religion beyond many Jews my age, being more zealous in the traditions of my ancestors.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 22:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15-16" />Biar bagitu ju, ma Tuhan Allah su putus ko kasi kanál Dia pung Ana sang beta. Beta pung mama balóm barana sang beta, te Dia su pili memang sang beta, tagal Dia mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta. Dia ju utus sang beta, ko pi ajar sang orang bukan Yahudi dong. Waktu Dia utus sang beta, beta sonde pi minta orang laen pung nasiat.<bt>Even though it was like that, nevertheless God decided to introduce His Child to me. My mother had not yet given birth to me, [te - contrary to expectation] He had already chose me beforehand, because He want to show his good liver to me. He also commissioned me, to go teach the non Yahudi people. When He commissioned me like that, I did not go request other people/person's advise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when the one who set me apart from birth, and called me by his grace, was pleased LITERALLY: to reveal his Son in me so that I might preach him among the non-Jews, immediately I did not consult any person,<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:3-6, 22:6-10, 26:13-18</note><v n="17" />Deng beta ju sonde pi katumu tua-tua Kristen yang su jadi memang Yesus pung utusan di Yerusalem. Ma beta jalan memang pi tana Arab. Ais itu, beta bale datang lai di kota Damsik.<bt>And I also did not go meet the Kristen elders who were already Yesus' apostles beforehand in Yerusalem. But I went straight away to Arab land. After that, I came back again to Damsik city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: nor did I go up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went into Arabia, and returned again to Damascus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tiga taon abis ju, beta pi katumu deng Petrus<bt>After three years, then I went to meet Petrus</bt><note reference="1:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani di ini ayat pake nama <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> Itu Petrus pung nama laen. Kefas tu, nama dalam bahasa Aram. Petrus tu, nama dalam bahasa Yunani. Ma itu dua nama pung arti sama. Andia &lt;&lt;batu&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Greek writing in this verse uses the name, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> That was Petrus' other name. That Kefas, is the name in Aram language. That Petrus, is the name in Greek language. But the meaning of those two names, are the same. That is 'rock'.</bt></note>di Yerusalem ko cari informasi dari dia. Ju beta tenga tahan di situ sampe lima blas hari.<bt>in Yerusalem to find/get information from him. And I stayed temporarily there for fifteen days. [EXEG: Gk /istorew/ “to visit, with the purpose of obtaining information” LN; “inquire, get information from” BADG. Note some commentators (e.g. Habermas) feel this Gk lexical choice is highly significant for a variety of reasons, so it's worth saying more than just ‘visit’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then after three years I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then after three years I went to Jerusalem to visit [and get information from] Cephas [Peter], and stayed with him fifteen days;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:26-30</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu waktu, beta ju katumu deng Tuhan Yesus pung adi barana, nama Yakobis. Ma beta sonde katumu deng Tuhan pung utusan yang laen dong. Cuma dong dua sa.<bt>At that time, I also met with the Lord Yesus' birth younger sibling (=not a cousin, but from same parent/s), named Yakobis. But I did not meet with God2's other apostles. Only just those two. [EXEG: LN notes that /adelphos/ with a meaning of ‘cousin’ is not attested, in spite of church tradition. NOTE to daughter translations: /adi/ is probably sufficient here, and would avoid unnecessary disputes with RC that might result in hesitance to use or promote the scriptures.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I didn't see other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I didn't see other apostles, only James, the brother of the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Apa yang beta tulis ni, memang batúl! Beta sonde putar-balek! Tuhan tau na!<bt>What I'm writing here, [it's] really true like that! I'm not twisting/decieving! God2 knows [+obvious]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Look, the things I write"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Look, the things I write to you, before God I am not lying.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu ju, beta bangun jalan pi propinsi Siria deng propinsi Kilikia.<bt>After that, then I got up and travelled to Siria province and Kilikia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then I came into the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then I came into the region of Syria and Cilicia.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Itu waktu, Kristus pung orang di Yudea dong balóm kanál sang beta.<bt>At that time, Kristus' people in Yudea did not know/had.not.met me yet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I was unknown personally to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I was unknown personally to the churches of Judea which are in Christ,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dong cuma dengar kabar bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu orang yang dolu bekin sangsara sang kotong tu, sakarang dia ada ajar Kristus pung Kabar Bae. Padahal dolu dia yang mau coba bekin ancor buang sang kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>They had only heard news saying, &lt;&lt;That aforementioned person who previously tormented us, now he is teaching Kristus' Good News. But.in.fact he is the one who previously wanted to try and completely destroy us.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They had only heard that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They had only heard that "The one who persecuted us before now preaches the Good News by faith which he once destroyed,"</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong samua angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan Allah, tagal beta su parcaya sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>Hearing like that, then they all *glorified (=elevated way up high) God, because I had believed in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and they glorified God because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and they glorified God because of me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung utusan laen dong tarima bae Paulus pung ajaran<bt>The Lord Yesus' other apostles accept well Paulus' teaching</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Ais lewat ampa blas taon ju, beta kambali lai pi kota Yerusalem sama-sama deng Barnabas. Deng botong ju ada bawa satu orang parcaya bukan Yahudi, nama Titus.<bt>Then after fourteen years, then I went back again to Yerusalem together with Barnabas. And we-exc also brought a non Yahudi believer, named Titus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anabainw: go up sumparalambanw: take along|i(1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anabainw: go up sumparalambanw: take along<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: After fourteen years I went up to Jerusalem again with Barnabas, taking Titus too;</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 11:30, 15:2</note><v n="2" />Beta pi sana tagal Tuhan Allah yang suru. Ais itu ju, beta carita kasi tua-tua Kristen dong, itu Kabar Bae yang beta su ajar sang orang bukan Yahudi dong. Itu waktu, beta omong sandiri sang dong, ko biar dong pareksa bae-bae apa yang beta ajar tu, batúl ko sonde. Te kalo dong putus bilang, sonde batúl, na, orang bisa bilang beta pung karjá parcuma sa!<bt>I went there because God is the one who ordered. After that, then I storied to the Kristen elders, that Good News which I had taught to the non Yahudi people. At that time, I spoke by myself with them, so that they could examine well that which I taught, [whether it was] true or not. Cuz if they decided that it was not true, na, people could say my work is just ineffectual/in.vain! [EXEG: TN: “so that what I do and have done in my work of telling the good news shall not be in vain/destroyed/ countered/ invalidated by others” F.F. Bruce: “What Paul was concerned about was not the validity of his gospel (of which he had divine assurance) but its practicability. His commission was not derived from Jerusalem, but it could not be executed effectively except in fellowship with Jerusalem.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokalupsis: revelation anatithemi: to declare, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">apokalupsis: revelation anatithemi: to declare, to explain, to set before someone, to communicate something<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>kerussw: to announce, to preach dokew: to seem, to be influential, to be recognized as being something, to have a reputation<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>me pws: lest somehow kenos: empty, useless, in vain, for nothing<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>trexw: run LITERALLY: but I went up by revelation, and explained to them the gospel which I preach among the nations, but privately to those who were of repute, lest somehow I was running or had run in vain.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dengar beta pung omong bagitu ju, dong tarima bae. Dong ju tarima bae sang Titus. Biar dia tu bukan orang Yahudi, ma dong sonde paksa dia sunat.<bt>Hearing my speaking like that, then they accepted [it]. They also accepted Titus. Even though he was a non Yahudi person, but they did not force him to get circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anagkazw: to force, to compel, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anagkazw: to force, to compel, to make someone do something peritemnw: to be circumcised<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: But even Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was not forced to be circumcised.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma itu waktu, ada barapa sodara yang sonde satuju, tagal dong ajar laen. Dong tu, Kristen putar-balek. Ais dong datang diam-diam ko mau paksa Yesus Kristus pung orang yang bukan Yahudi, ko iko orang Yahudi pung atoran agama samua. Padahal Yesus Kristus su kasi bebas sang kotong, andia ko kotong su sonde ta'ika lai deng itu atoran dong, sama ke budak.<bt>But at that time, there were several siblings who did not agree [NOTE to daughter translations: fill in object “with my teaching” if necessary], because they taught differently. They are false/deceptive Kristen. So they came quietly/secretly to force Yesus Kristus' people who are not Yahudi, to follow all the Yahudi people's religious regulations. But.in.actual.fact Yesus Kristus has freed us-inc, that is why we-inc are no longer tied to those regulations, like a slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareisaktos: sneak in pseudadelphos: false brother|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">pareisaktos: sneak in pseudadelphos: false brother<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>pareisepxomai: slip in kataskopew: spy out<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eleutheria: freedom, liberty [from slavery to the law] katadoulow: to make slaves, to enslave, to bring into bondage<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: But because of false brothers who sneaked in secretly, slipping in to spy out our freedom which we have in Christ Jesus, in order to make us slaves;</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Biar dong paksa bagitu, ma botong sonde mau tarima sadiki ju. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa parcaya tarús itu Kabar Bae yang beta su ajar. Te itu memang batúl.<bt>Even though they forced like that, but we-inc did not accept even a little. Because of that, you can continue to believe that aforementioned Good News which I have taught. Cuz it is truly true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eixw: yield, give in, submit hupotage:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">eixw: yield, give in, submit hupotage: subjection, submission<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>diamenw: remain, stay, continue LITERALLY: We did not give in to them for a moment, so that the truth of the gospel might remain for you.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Itu tua-tua dong tarima bae beta pung ajaran tu, deng dong sonde tamba apa-apa lai. Ma Tuhan Allah sonde bapili muka. Jadi biar dong orang bésar ko, kici ko, bukan itu yang pantíng.<bt>Those elders accepted my aforementioned teaching, and they did not add anything else. But God does not discriminate. So (consequently), whether they or big/important people or small not, that's not what is important.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hopoios: what kind, what sort diapherw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">hopoios: what kind, what sort diapherw: to make a difference, to matter<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>lambanw: receive prosanatithemi: to add<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: and from those who seemed to be [important / leaders]--what kind they were makes no difference to me--God does not receive a man by appearances--they added nothing to me,</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 10:17</note><v n="7" />Te yang pantíng, andia: dong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang beta ko pi bawa Kabar Bae kasi orang bukan Yahudi. Sama ke Dia ju utus sang Petrus ko pi bawa itu Kabar Bae kasi orang Yahudi.<bt>Cuz what is important, is this: they know that, God has already chosen me to go take Good News to non Yahudi people. The same as He also commisioned Petrus to go take that Good News to Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enantion: before akrobustia: heathenism, paganism, Gentiles|i(7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">enantion: before akrobustia: heathenism, paganism, Gentiles<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: but on the contrary, they saw that I was entrusted to the heathen, just as Peter to the circumcised,</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te Tuhan Allah su kasi kuasa sang Petrus ko jadi utusan kasi orang Yahudi. Bagitu ju Dia kasi kuasa sang beta ko jadi utusan kasi orang bukan Yahudi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God has given power/authority to Petrus to become an apostle for the Yahudi people. Like that also He gave power/authority to me to become an apostle for the non Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="energew: to work, to be at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">energew: to work, to be at work, to operate, to be effective LITERALLY: for the one who worked in Peter for an apostleship to the circumcised, worked in me to the Gentiles.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Itu waktu, orang su anggap Yakobis, Petrus,<bt>At that time, people already considered Yakobis, Petrus</bt><note reference="2:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani di ini ayat pake nama, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> Itu Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Greek language writing in this verse uses the name, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> That is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>deng Yohanis, pamimpin gareja. Waktu dong tiga dapa tau bilang, Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta, ju dong bangun badiri ko datang pegang tangan sang beta deng Barnabas, ko jadi tanda bilang, botong samua su satu hati. Dong satuju ko botong pi bawa Kabar Bae kasi orang bukan Yahudi, deng dong yang pi bawa kasi orang Yahudi.<bt>and Yohanis, church leaders. When the three of them found out that God has shown His good liver to me, then they stood up to come shake hands with me and Barnabas, to become a sign/signal that we-exc all were of one liver (=in agreement). They agreed for us to go take the Good News to the non Yahudi people, and they [would be the ones] who go take it to the Yahudi people. [NOTE to daughter translations: “they stood up to come shake hands with me” is to emphasize the honour of extending the “right hand of fellowship”; initiated by the important people; but be careful that it doesn't convey the impression that they left one location and went to another.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and when they knew [of]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and when they knew [of] the grace that was given to me, James and Cephas and John, who seemed to be pillars, gave me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcision;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Cuma ada satu hal yang dong kasi inga sang botong. Andia, botong jang lupa tolong sang orang miskin dong. Memang itu yang beta su mau bekin.<bt>There was just one matter which they reminded me of, that is that we-exc don't forget to help the poor people. That is truly what I already want to do. [EXEG: TN “This phrase refers to the Christians living in Jerusalem. They were having a difficult time getting enough food.” BUT, the jury is still out on this, and I find no version in any major language I know that tries to make that explicit. Some relate these verses to Acts 11, others link it to Acts 15; Some commentators on Paul's apostleship (assuming Acts 15) see this as selective memory, highlighting only one of the things in the circular letter sent at the end of Acts 15. (And in Acts 15 it is clearly a general principle, not focused on a particular group of people in strife.) Others see this as highlighting the prominent issue which shows Paul's commitment to unity in the church over the Jew/Gentile issue which is a central theme of Galatians (see also discussion on F.F. Bruce on this whole passage and problems with interpreting the visit/s to Jerusalem and meeting/s with apostles). Our protocol in Timor is to preserve the ambiguity where possible, and where both interpretations are supported.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: only they would have us"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: only they would have us remember the poor, which very thing I was eager to do.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus togor sang Petrus di Antiokia, tagal dia ondor dari orang bukan Yahudi dong<bt>Paulus rebukes Petrus in Antiokia, because he distanced himself from non Yahudi people</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added to title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** added to title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais satu kali Petrus datang di kota Antiokia, ju beta togor sang dia taráng-taráng, tagal dia ada bekin sala.<bt>Then one time Petrus come to Antiokia city, then I rebuked him clearly, because he was doing wrong. [NOTE to daughter translations: this is about Peter's teaching, not about stealing or adultery, so make sure “doing wrong” doesn't lean toward the latter.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antistemi: to be set against, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">antistemi: to be set against, to oppose kataginwskw: to condemn, to accuse, to pronounce guilty<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: But when Cephas came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he stood condemned.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Waktu dia baru datang, dia sanáng dudu makan sama-sama deng Kristus pung orang yang bukan Yahudi dong. Ma waktu Yakobis pung tamán orang Yahudi dong datang, ju Petrus ondor diri dari sodara bukan Yahudi, deng sonde dudu makan lai deng dong. Te dia taku sang itu orang Yahudi yang ajar bilang, Kristus pung orang dong musti bapegang kuat orang Yahudi pung atoran agama samua, deng musti idop tapisa dari orang bukan Yahudi dong.<bt>When he had just come, he was happy to sit eating together with Kristus' non Yahudi people. But then Yakobis' Yahudi people friends come, then Petrus reversed himself (=backed away) from the non Yahudi siblings, and did not sit and eat anymore with them. Cuz he was afraid of those Yahudi people who teach saying, Kristus' people must tightly hold (=follow) all the Yahudi people's religious regulations, and [they] must live separated from non Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunesthiw: to eat with hupostellw: to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">sunesthiw: to eat with hupostellw: to withdraw, to go back from<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>aphorizw: to separate phobew: to fear, to be afraid<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: For before certain ones came from James, he ate with the Gentiles; but when they came, he withdrew and separated himself, fearing the circumcision party</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Lia Petrus pung bekin-bekin tu, orang Yahudi laen dong ju iko-iko. Sampe Barnabas ju iko tamaso deng dong pung muka-balakang tu.<bt>Seeing Petrus' aforementioned nonsense, other Yahudi people also followed along. To the point that Barnabas also followed along with that front-back (=hypocrisy) of theirs. [NOTE to daughter translations (ALT): say different, do different.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunupokrinomai: to join in pretending, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">sunupokrinomai: to join in pretending, to join in hypocrisy sunapagw: to carry away, to yield, to lead away, to lead astray<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>hupokrisis: hypocrisy LITERALLY: The rest of the Jews joined him in hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was led astray by their hypocrisy.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma waktu beta lia dong su sonde iko batúl Kabar Bae pung mau, ju beta togor memang sang Petrus di dong pung muka bilang, &lt;&lt;We, bu Pe'u! Bu ni, memang orang Yahudi. Ma Tuhan Allah su buka jalan ko orang yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus jang ta'ika lai deng orang Yahudi pung atoran agama dong. Deng bu su tarima itu hal. Ais karmana ko sakarang bu masi mau paksa orang yang bukan Yahudi, ko dong bekin diri sama ke orang Yahudi lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>But when I saw that they did not correctly follow the Good New's intent, then I right away scolded Petrus in front of them saying, &lt;&lt;We, [+get attention] elder.brother Pete! Elder brother here (=you), is truly/certainly a Yahudi person. But God has opened the way so that people who believe in Yesus Kristus are no longer tied with the Yahudi people's religious regulations. And older.brother (=you) have accepted that. So then how is it that now older.brother (=you) still wants to force non Yahudi people so that they make themselves like Yahudi people again?&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: see note at end of vs.21.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orthopodeoo: be straightforward, be unwavering, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">orthopodeoo: be straightforward, be unwavering, be sincere in conduct LITERALLY: But when I saw that they were not straightforward about the truth of the gospel, I said to Peter in front of them all, "If you, being a Jew, live like a Gentile and not like a Jew, how come you force the Gentiles to live like Jews?"<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan Allah su buka jalan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Ma Tuhan Allah su buka jalan ko orang yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus jang ta'ika lai deng orang Yahudi pung atoran agama dong. Ais, karmana ko bu masi mau paksa orang yang bukan Yahudi, ko dong bekin diri sama ke orang Yahudi lai?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Beta togor sang Petrus bagitu, tagal botong dua sama-sama orang Yahudi. Botong pung bangsa Yahudi sonde sama ke suku-bangsa laen dong, tagal botong pung bangsa su lama kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>I scolded/rebuked Petrus like that, because the two of us were both Yahudi people. Our Yahudi nation is not the same as other nations, because our nation has already known God for a long time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We who are Jews by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We who are Jews by birth, and not Gentile sinners,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma sakarang kotong ju tau bilang, Tuhan sonde tarima bae satu orang ju, tagal dia bekin iko atoran agama. Te Tuhan tarima bae orang, kalo dia parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, bukan tagal dia bekin iko atoran agama. Bagitu baru Tuhan cap orang bilang, dia sonde ada pung sala lai.<bt>But now we-inc also know that, God2 does not accept even one person, because s/he acts according to religious regulations. Cuz (elaboration) God2 accepts a person, if s/he believes Yesus Kristus, not because s/he acts according to relgious regulations. Like that, only then does God2 stamp/brand/ categorise a person as innocent (=no longer having wrong/sin). [NOTE to daughter translations: beginning from here, /Tuhan tarima bae/ is a theological term for ‘justified’, whereas earlier /tarima bae/ was just the manner in which the other apostles accepted Paul. You are looking for something akin to BI ‘dibenarkan Allah’. It works in Kupang, but be careful it doesn't miss the point by going literal from the Kupang. (ALT) Dhao uses “accepts him as a straight/right person”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: knowing that a person is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: knowing that a person is not justified by the works of the law, but by faith in Jesus Christ, and we trust in Christ Jesus, so that we are justified by faith in Christ, and not be the works of the law, because by the works of the law no human being is justified.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 143:2, Roma 3:20, 22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Andia ko kotong ajar bilang, Tuhan tarima bae sang orang, tagal dia parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Ma ada orang Yahudi yang tudu sang botong bilang, botong su sala, tagal botong parcaya sang Kristus, ma sonde pegang lai atoran agama Yahudi dong. Bosong ju mau lempar sala bagitu, ko?<bt>That's why we-inc teach that God accepts a person because s/he believes in Yesus Kristus. But there are Yahudi people who accuse us-ex saying we-exc are wrong, because we believe in Kristus, but don't hold the Yahudi religious regulations anymore. Do you also want to throw an accusation like that, [+tag question]?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if in our attempt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if in our attempt to be justified in Christ, we ourselves are found to be sinners, then is Christ a servant of sin? Certainly not!</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te kalo beta pegang ame kambali itu atoran agama yang beta su lapás buang tu, na, itu baru beta sala!<bt>Cuz if I hold again those aforementioned religious regulations which I have already gotten free of, well then I'll be wrong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu, dia pung nama, beta jilat/lambe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">itu, dia pung nama, beta jilat/lambe kambali beta pung luda ; lambe = lick</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataluw: destroy oikodomew: build up|i(18) (18)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">kataluw: destroy oikodomew: build up<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>parabates: transgression, break the law sunistemi: demonstrate, prove<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: For if I rebuild the things which I destroyed, I prove that I am a lawbreaker.</Message></Annotation><v n="19-20" />Memang dolu beta usaha karás bekin iko atoran agama Yahudi dong, ko biar beta babae deng Tuhan. Ma beta sonde bisa-bisa ju. Andia ko sakarang beta su lapás buang itu atoran dong ko idop ta'ika deng Kristus. Deng bagitu, baru Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang beta. Anggap sa, beta su mati tapaku di kayu palang sama-sama deng Kristus. Sakarang bukan beta yang idop lai, ma Kristus yang ada idop dalam beta pung diri. Beta dapa idop yang baru ni, tagal beta parcaya sang Tuhan pung Ana. Te Dia sayang talalu sang beta, sampe Dia mati ganti beta.<bt>It's true that previously I tried to act according to the Yahudi religious regulations, so that I cold be in a reciprocally.good.relationship with God2. But I could not even possibly do it. That's why now I have let go/gotten rid of those regulations to live tied to Kristus. In doing like that, only then will God accept me. Just regard it as if, I have died nailed to the cross together with Kristus. Now it's not me who lives anymore, but Kristus who lives in my self/being. I got this life which is new, because I believe in God2's Child. Cuz (elaboration) he greatly loves me, to.the.point that He died replacing me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***19-20 bridged"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">***19-20 bridged</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For through the law, I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For through the law, I died to the law, that I might live to God. LITERALLY: I have been crucified with Christ. It is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me. And the life that I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself for me.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais Tuhan Allah tarima sang beta tagal Dia pung hati bae, bukan tagal beta iko atoran agama dong. Te kalo orang bisa babae deng Tuhan tagal iko atoran agama, na, itu dia pung arti bilang, Kristus pung mati tu, parcuma sa.<bt>So (consequently) God receives me because of His good liver (*mercy/grace/), not because I follow religious regulations. Cuz if people could be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because of following religious regulations, well that would mean that, that death of Kristus' was just pointless/in.vain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not nullify the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not nullify the grace of God. For if righteousness could be gained through the law, Christ died for nothing.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu tu, yang beta kasi tau sang Petrus dong di Antiokia.<bt>That there, is what I told to Petrus them (collective) in Antiokia. [DISCOURSE structure: There are varying opinions of what Paul says to Peter. Just vs. 14? vs. 14-18? All the way to vs. 14-21? MC and NIV favour the whole lot (NIV note at 21 says some end quote at 14). Fung argues “Structurally speaking, these verses (15-21) are, a continuation of Paul’s address to Peter which began with v. 14b,..” There is no semantic or grammatical basis to stop at 18 (even though TH and TN refer to that shorter grouping). 19-21 are an expansion/elaboration (introduced by /gar/ and working with the same concepts and vocab) of the previous verses--see NRSV, NLT, CEV, NET, GW, NCV. So it's either 14 alone, or 14-21. TN says “It is important to understand that these words are spoken by a Jew to a Jew in front of other Jews. If Paul had had the opportunity to rebuke the Judaizers who had come to confuse the Galatians, his rebuke would have been very similar. Since it is not possible to rebuke those false teachers directly, Paul does it indirectly. This is also an indirect rebuke to the Galatian Gentile believers, who had been influenced by this wrong teaching.” TH says without certainty “These verses do not seem to be addressed to Peter alone, but to a wider audience.... The problem is hard to resolve.” Bruce (2:15) acknowledges “It is difficult to decide at what point Paul's quotation of his rebuke to Peter comes to an end and passes into his general exposition of the principle at stake. He probably summarizes his rebuke to Peter and the develops its implications, thus passing smoothly from the personal occasion to the universal principle,...”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang kotong, tagal kotong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus<bt>God accepts us, because we believe in Yesus Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />We! Orang Galatia dong! Dolu beta sandiri su kasi tau di bosong pung muka idong, so'al Yesus Kristus pung mati di kayu palang. Ma sakarang orang su tipu manta-manta sang bosong! Bosong pung bodo lai!<bt>We! [+get attention] Galatia people! Previously I myself have explain in your faces noses (=explained directly to you) about Yesus Kristus' death on the cross. But now people have easily decieved you! Your stupidity is too much!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tipu manta-manta = talalu gampang kana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">tipu manta-manta = talalu gampang kana tipu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anoetos: unintelligent, foolish baskainw: to bewitch,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anoetos: unintelligent, foolish baskainw: to bewitch, hex, cast a spell on<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>peithw: to obey prographw: to present clearly to, to portray to, to describe plainly, to openly display<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>staurow: to crucify LITERALLY: O foolish Galatians! Who has bewitched you that you do not obey the truth? Jesus Christ was clearly presented as crucified before your eyes.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta cuma mau tanya satu hal. Bosong tarima ame Tuhan pung Roh, tagal bosong iko atoran agama, ko? Sonde, to! Dia pung Roh datang sang bosong, tagal bosong parcaya Kabar Bae yang bosong su dengar.<bt>I only want to ask one thing. Did you receive that Spirit of God2's, because you followed religious regulations, [+tag question]? Of course not, right! His Sprit came to you, because you believed that Good News which you had heard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akoe: report manthanw: find out, learn|i(2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">akoe: report manthanw: find out, learn<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: This only I would like to find out from you: Did you receive the Spirit by doing the Law, or by hearing with faith?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jadi akurang ko bosong su bodo talalu bagitu, é? Dolu bosong su idop iko Roh Barisi pung mau. Ma sakarang bosong su bale lai ko idop iko manusia pung mau.<bt>So (consequently), why are so stupid like that? Previously you lived according to the Holy Spirit's will. But now you have turned again to live according to human's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitelew: to finish, to end, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">epitelew: to finish, to end, to complete something, to perfect LITERALLY: Are you so foolish? After starting with the Spirit, are you finishing by the flesh?<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu bosong baru mulai parcaya sang Kristus, bosong dapa siksa bam-banya. Jang sampe itu samua jadi parcuma sa! (Padahal parcaya sang Kristus sonde parcuma.)<bt>When you just began to believe in Kristus, you received much torture/abuse. Don't let it be that all of that become pointless! (When in fact, believing in Kristus cannot be pointless.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasxw: to experience, to undergo, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">pasxw: to experience, to undergo, to suffer eike: in vain, for nothing<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: Have you experienced so many things in vain? If it is in vain.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Waktu Tuhan Allah kasi Dia pung Roh, deng kasi tunju tanda heran macam-macam di bosong pung muka, bosong pikir Dia bekin bagitu tagal bosong iko atoran agama, ko? Sonde, to! Dia bekin bagitu, tagal bosong parcaya Kabar Bae yang bosong su dengar.<bt>When God gave His Spirit, and showed those various kinds of miracles in front of you, did you think He did like that because you follow religious regulations, [+tag question]? Of course not, right! He did like that, because you believed that Good News which you had heard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epixoregew: give plenty, supply abundantly LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">epixoregew: give plenty, supply abundantly LITERALLY: Therefore, he who gives the Spirit to you, and does miracles among you, does he do it by the deeds of the Law, or by hearing with faith?<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Inga orang Yahudi pung moyang, andia ba'i Abraham. Te Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal dia parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, andia ko Tuhan tarima bae sang dia, deng cap sang dia, orang hati lurus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember the Yahudi people's ancestor, that is Gf/Ff Abraham. Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures write saying, “Because he believed in God, that's why God2 accepted him, and stamped/branded him as a straight-livered person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="logizomai: to count, to reckon LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">logizomai: to count, to reckon LITERALLY: Just as Abraham trusted God, and it was counted to him as righteousness.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:6, Roma 4:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi bosong musti mangarti bae-bae ini hal! Orang yang parcaya, sama ke Abraham, dong jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang yang batúl.<bt>So you must understand this matter well! People who believe, like Abraham, they become God's true people. [EXEG: TN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then know this, that those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then know this, that those who believe, they are children of Abraham.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani asli tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;dong jadi Abraham pung ana-ana&gt;&gt;. Orang Yahudi biasa pake istila &lt;Abraham pung ana-ana&gt; deng maksud bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah pung orang dong&gt;. Lia <span class="Italic">Roma</span> 4:16 ju.<bt>The original Greek language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;they became Abraham's children&gt;&gt;. The Yahudi people often use the term Abraham's children with the meaning of God's children. See also Roma 4:16.</bt></note><v n="8" />Tuhan su kasi tau memang dalam Dia pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, nanti Dia ju tarima orang dari suku-bangsa laen dong bilang, dong orang hati lurus, kalo dong parcaya sang Dia. Te dolu-dolu Dia su kasi tau memang Kabar Bae sang ba'i Abraham bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti samua suku-bangsa di dunya dapa berkat tagal lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>God2 told beforehand in His Holy Writing that, later He would also receive people from other nations/races saying they were straight-livered people (just, righteous), if/when they believed in Him. Cuz long ago He already foretold Good News to Abraham saying, &lt;&lt;Later all nations on earth will receive blessing because of you.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dikaiow: to justify, to make right,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">dikaiow: to justify, to make right, to make right with God eneulogew: to bless<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>proeuaggelizomai: proclaim in advance, preach ahead of time prooraw: see previously, see in advance, see ahead of time<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: And the Scripture, forseeing that God would justify the nations by faith, preached before the Good News to Abraham, saying, "In you shall all the nations be blessed".</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 12:3</note><v n="9" />Tagal Tuhan Allah pung janji tu, andia ko Dia ju kasi berkat sang samua orang yang parcaya sang Dia, sama ke yang Dia su kasi sang Abraham.<bt>Because of that promise of God's, that's why He also give blessing to all people who believe in Him, just like He already gave to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogew: to bless LITERALLY: So those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">eulogew: to bless LITERALLY: So those who believe are blessed with Abraham, who believed.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Orang yang iko atoran agama ko biar Tuhan tarima bae sang dia, na, dia musti pikol barát itu atoran samua, sama ke dia su kaná kutuk. Te ada tatulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang sonde iko tarús-tarús atoran agama sampe alus-alus, dia kaná kutuk!&gt;&gt;<bt>A person who follows religious regulations so that God2 will accept him/her, na, s/he must heavily shoulder.carry all those regulations, just like s/he has been cursed. Cuz it is written in God's Holy Writing saying, &lt;&lt;The person who does not continually follow religious regulations down to the last detail, s/he is cursed!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Because of local worldviews, be careful to distinguish between “being cursed/under a curse” (= the punishment/bad things are already happening) from “being cursed/living under a curse/having a curse hanging over you” (=we know bad things will happen, but it hasn't started yet); TH describes it as “It is rather the threat of condemnation which continues for any person who thinks that he can become right with God by obeying the Law. Therefore, one may translate live under a curse as "continue under threat of being condemned," or "live all the time knowing that God will condemn them."” Kupang can signal the distinction with /sama ke/ “like/as if”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katara: curse epikataratos: cursed, be under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">katara: curse epikataratos: cursed, be under divine wrath, awaiting the final destruction<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>emmenw: persevere in, stand by, be careful to obey LITERALLY: For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse. For it has been written, &lt;&lt;Cursed is everyone who does not continue to do all things which have been written in the book of the Law.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 27:26</note><v n="11" />Ma su jalás, Tuhan Allah sonde tarima orang <span class="Italic">tagal </span>dia iko atoran agama. Te ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang musti parcaya sang Beta, baru Beta tarima bae sang dia ke orang hati lurus, ko dia dapa idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>But it is already clear, God does not receive a person, because s/he follows religious regulations. Cuz it written saying, &lt;&lt;A person must believe in Me, before I will accept him/her as a straight/righteous person, so that s/he can get/have true life.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="delos: be clear LITERALLY: It is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">delos: be clear LITERALLY: It is clear that no person is justified by the Law in God's sight, for, "The one who is justified by faith will live."<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko dia dapa idop tarús."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">ko dia dapa idop tarús.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 2:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Naa! Kalo orang mau idop iko atoran agama pung mau, dia musti bekin iko samua-samua sampe alus-alus! Te Tuhan su kasi tau memang dalam Dia pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau idop iko atoran, nanti dia batasibu sa deng itu atoran dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>So! If a person wants to live according to the way of religious regulations, s/he must do according to them all down to the last detail! Cuz God2 has foretold in His Holy Writing saying, &lt;&lt;The person who lives following regulations, later s/he will be totally preoccupied with those regulations.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Law is not based"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Law is not based on believing; but, "The person who does these things will live by them."</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 18:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma Kristus su bayar putus, ko kasi bebas sang botong dari itu atoran agama yang ada ika sang botong. Dolu botong idop satenga mati deng pikol barát itu atoran agama, sama ke orang yang kaná kutuk. Ma sakarang Tuhan Yesus su angka itu kutuk dari botong. Te ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mati tagantong di pohon, dia kaná kutuk.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Kristus has completely paid to free us-ex from those religious regulations which are binding/tieing us-ex. Previously we-exc lived half dead (=with great trouble/effort) by heavily shoulder.carrying those religious regulations like a person who is cursed. But now the Lord Yesus has lifted that curse from us. Cuz it is written in the Holy Writing saying, &lt;&lt;The person who dies hanging on a tree, s/he is cursed.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk. hung on tree, not cross here; TB cross. Hung from any tree or wooden structure. Not specifically the cross of Christ. The Jewish idea was that if the body of an executed criminal or a murder victim were publicly exposed by hanging it from a tree or post, that would defile the land. When Roman crucifixion came along later, that was a natural extension of a much older idea.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Both subject and object fronted, no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">Both subject and object fronted, no connector (asyndeton). Sudden break, going off in another direction now. Up to this point, he's almost been going around in circles talking about how we can't get free. The implicit bridge, "we can't do it," needs to be before the verse break, not after it. Putting it in Verse 12 is natural, and allows 13 to start with a bang like the Greek does. exagorazw: to redeem, to buy back, to release, to free by paying for<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>epikataratos: cursed katathema: accursed thing<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katara: curse epi xylou: hung from any tree or wooden structure. Not specifically the cross of Christ. The Jewish idea was that if the body of an executed criminal or a murder victim were publicly exposed by hanging it from a tree or post, that would defile the land. When Roman crucifixion came along later, that was a natural extension of a much older idea.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: Christ has redeemed us from the curse of the Law, becoming a curse for us, because it has been written "Cursed is everyone who hangs on a cross,"</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 21:23</note><v n="14" />Waktu Yesus Kristus mati ko kasi salamat sang kotong, itu berkat yang Tuhan Allah su kasi sang Abraham, turun datang di suku-bangsa laen dong ju. Deng bagitu, samua orang yang parcaya sang Kristus bisa tarima Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Dia su janji.<bt>When Yesus Kristus died to save us-inc, that blessing which God had already given to Abraham, then came down to the other nations. In that way, all people who believe Kristus can receive that Spirit of God's which He has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that the blessing of Abraham"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles by Christ Jesus, that we may receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pegang karás Dia pung janji<bt>God holds tight to His promise</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Sodara dong! Sakarang beta mau pake conto dari kotong pung idop hari-hari. Kalo ada orang tulis ame surat warisan, ais dia su teken dia pung nama di itu surat, itu surat su sah. Orang laen su sonde bisa kasi batal apa yang tatulis dalam itu surat, deng su sonde bisa tulis tamba apa-apa lai di situ.<bt>Siblings! Now I want to use an example from our-in everyday lives. If a person writes an inheritance letter, then s/he signs his/her name on that letter, that letter is legal. Another person cannot cancel what is written in that letter, and cannot write adding anything else there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="athetew: set aside, displace diatheke: last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">athetew: set aside, displace diatheke: last will and testament, a will that has been ratified<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>epidiatassomai: add a codicil kurow: confirm, ratify, validate, put into effect, establish<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Brothers, I speak with a human example: even a person's will, if ratified, nobody can cancel it or add to it.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Bagitu ju, waktu Tuhan Allah ika janji deng Abraham deng dia pung turunan. Tuhan Allah sonde bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta bekin janji ni deng lu pung turunan dong&gt;&gt;, tagal Dia sonde janji kasi orang bam-banya. Ma Dia cuma janji kasi Abraham pung turunan satu orang sa, andia Kristus.<bt>Like that also, when God bound/established a promise with Abraham and his descendant. God did not say &lt;&lt;I make this promise with your descendants&gt;&gt;, because He did not promise to lots of people. But He only promised to just one descendant of Abraham, that is Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** streamlined ftn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** streamlined ftn</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now to Abraham and his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now to Abraham and his offspring the promises were made. It doesn't say, "and to your children", which are many, but to one, "and to your son", which is Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;sonde bilang &lt;ika janji deng lu pung bibit dong (jamak)&gt;&gt;&gt;, ma &lt;&lt;deng lu pung bibit (tunggal)&gt;&gt;. Dalam janji ni, kata bahasa Yunani &lt;&lt;bibit&gt;&gt; pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;turunan&gt;&gt;. Lia ju di <span class="Italic">Carita Mula-mula</span> 12:7.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, “doesn't say ‘bind a promise with your-sg seeds (plural)’, but ‘with your seed (singular)’.” In this promise here, the Yunani word “seed” means “descendant”. See also at Genesis 12:7.</bt></note><v n="17" />Beta pung maksud bagini: Tuhan Allah bekin janji lebe dolu deng ba'i Abraham. Ais ampa ratus tiga pulu taon, baru Dia kasi turun atoran agama kasi orang Yahudi dong, lewat dong pung ba'i Musa. Biar bagitu ju, ma Tuhan sonde kasi batal Dia pung janji yang Dia bekin lebe dolu.<bt>My meaning is like this: God made a promise first/beforehand with Gf Abraham. After four hundred thirty years, then He sent down the religious regulations to the Yahudi people, through/by means of their Gf Musa. Even though it was like that, nevertheless God2 did not cancel that promise of His which He had made previously.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akurow: make void, annul, cancel katargew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">akurow: make void, annul, cancel katargew: make ineffective<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>prokurow: ratify previously, confirm ahead of time LITERALLY: This is what I mean, that the covenant, which was ratified before by God about Christ, the Law, which was given four hundred and thirty years later, cannot cancel, to make the promise null and void.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:40</note><v n="18" />Te Tuhan sonde kasi berkat sang Abraham tagal dia ada bekin iko atoran. Ma Dia kasi berkat tagal Dia su janji memang ko mau parsén kasi sang Abraham dari dolu. Itu sama ke satu ana yang tarima pusaka dari dia pung bapa. Dia tarima tagal dia pung bapa su janji memang, bukan tagal itu ana ada bekin iko atoran.<bt>Cuz God2 did not give blessing to Abraham because he followed regulations. But He gave blessing because He had pre-promised to give a gift to Abraham from long before. That is like a child who receives an inheritance from his father. He receives [it] because his father had pre-promised, not because that child acts according to regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleronomia: inheritance xarizomai: give freely|i(18) (18)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">kleronomia: inheritance xarizomai: give freely<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: For if the inheritance be from the Law, then it is not by promise; but God gave it to Abraham by promise.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo orang bisa tarima dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Kalo orang bisa tarima dia pung bapa pung harta tagal dia iko atoran, na, dia pung bapa sonde parlú janji apa-apa dalam surat warisan. Bagitu ju deng Abraham. Dia sonde tarima berkat tagal dia ada bekin apa-apa. Dia tarima tagal Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 4:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Naa! Sakarang beta mau tanya bagini: kalo Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang ba'i Abraham tagal dia pung parcaya, akurang ko Tuhan kasi tamba lai atoran agama lewat ba'i Musa? Dia tamba atoran agama dong ko ajar manusia so'al dong pung sala macam-macam. Dia pung maksud ko manusia idop iko itu atoran pung mau, sampe Abraham pung turunan satu tu datang. Ais kalo itu turunan, andia Kristus su datang, itu atoran su sonde parlú lai.<bt>So! Now I want to ask like this: if God accepted Gf/Ff Abraham because of his belief, why did God2 give adding on religious regualtions via/by Gf/Ff Musa? He added religious regulations to teach humans about their different kinds of wrongs. His intent was that humans live according to the will/intent of those regulations, until that one descendant of Abraham came. Then when that descendant, that is the Kristus had come, those regulations were no longer needed anymore. [NOTE to daughter translations: if the word for “descendants in your language is seen as inherently plural, the next to the last sentence should be OK, but in the last sentence substitute “that person".]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prostithemi: to add parabasis: to overstep,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">prostithemi: to add parabasis: to overstep, to transgress<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>diatassw: order, direct, command diatage: ordinance, direction<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>mesites: mediator, intermediary, representative, arbitrator, lawyer, LITERALLY: Why, then, the Law? It was added because of transgressions until the Child to whom the promise referred had come. The Law was handed down through angels by the hands of a mediator.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Tuhan kasi itu atoran agama Yahudi, Dia sonde kasi langsung memang. Ma Dia pake Dia pung ana bua dari sorga, ais dong bawa datang kasi di ba'i Musa pung tangan, baru Musa kasi pi orang Yahudi. Deng bagitu, Musa jadi jambatan kasi Tuhan deng Dia pung orang dong.<bt>When God2 gave those Yahudi religious regulations, he did not give them directly. But He used His underlings from heaven (*angels), then they brought them to Musa's hand, then Musa gave them to the Yahudi people. In that manner, Musa became a bridge for God and His people. [NOTE to daughter translations: if first sentence not clear, add object: “to the Jewish people.”]</bt><v n="20" />Ma waktu Tuhan Allah bekin janji deng Abraham, Dia sonde pake jambatan. Ko Dia sandiri yang janji langsung na! Deng bagitu, kotong tau bilang, Tuhan pung janji tu, lebe hebat dari itu atoran dong.<bt>But when God made a promise with Abraham, He did not use a bridge. Because obvious it was He himself who promised directly. In that manner, we-inc know that, that promise of God's is more awesome/great than those regulations. [EXEG: Translators Notes, Yakan BT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@CEV missed this one badly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">@@CEV missed this one badly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now, a mediator is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now, a mediator is not a mediator of one, but God is one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Atoran agama ajar manusia so'al dong pung sala macam-macam<bt>Religious regulations teach humans about their various kinds of wrong</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Waktu Tuhan kasi itu atoran agama sang ba'i Musa, itu bamalawan deng Dia pung janji-janji, ko? Sonde! Te kalo ada atoran yang manusia bisa bekin iko, ko Tuhan tarima bae sang dia ko biar dia bisa idop, tantu orang Yahudi pung atoran bisa bekin bagitu. Padahal sonde ada atoran satu ju yang manusia bisa bekin iko, ko bekin dingin Tuhan pung hati, ko biar Tuhan tarima bae sang dia.<bt>When God2 gave those religious regulations to Gf/Ff Musa, did that oppose/be.in.contradiction.to his promises, [+tag question]? Of course not! Cuz if there are regulations which a human can follow, in order for God2 to accept him/her so s/he can live, surely the Yahudi people's regualtions could do like that. But in actual fact there is not a single regulation which a human can follow, to cool God2's liver, so that God2 will accept him/her. (cool God's liver = make God no longer angry -- not in a bad sense but from justifiable anger) [EXEG: NRSV, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added “so s/he can live”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** added “so s/he can live”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zwopoiew: make alive LITERALLY: Is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">zwopoiew: make alive LITERALLY: Is the Law then against the promises of God? Certainly not! For if there could have been a Law given which could have given life, surely righteousness would have been given by the Law.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, samua orang ada ta'ika mati deng sala macam-macam. Andia ko cuma orang yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus sa, yang bisa tarima apa yang Tuhan Allah su janji.<bt>Cuz in God2's Holy Writing it is written saying, all people are completely bound/tied.up with all.kinds.of wrongs. That's why only just a person who believes Yesus Kristus, is the one who can receive that which God has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: God proves that people have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">hina: God proves that people have all sinned, in order to make it clear that their deeds are inadequate and trusting him is the only recourse. sugkleiw: be enclosed, be imprisoned [see verse 24]<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: But the Scripture declares that all are prisoners of sin, so that what was promised, being given through faith in Jesus Christ, might be given to those who believe.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu Kristus balóm datang, botong orang Yahudi ta'ika mati deng itu atoran dong sampe sonde bisa talapás. Ma sampe dia pung waktu, Tuhan buka jalan ko botong bebas dari itu atoran dong, kalo botong parcaya sang Kristus.<bt>When Kristus had not yet come, we-exc Yahudi people were completely bound/tied up with those regulations to the point that we could not be unbound/freed. But when the time arrived, God2 opened the path so that we-exc could be free from those regulations, if we-exc believe Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phrourew: be confined, be held under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">phrourew: be confined, be held under custody be the law, be under guard sugkleiw: be enclosed, be imprisoned, keep under restraint [see v 22]<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: But before faith came, we were kept under the Law, shut up unto the faith which would afterward be revealed.</Message></Annotation><v n="24-25" />Jadi itu atoran agama dong tu, conto ke tukang jaga yang ajar bae-bae sang kotong sampe Kristus datang. Ma kalo Dia su datang, na, baru kotong bisa parcaya sang Dia, ko idop babae deng Tuhan Allah. Andia ko sakarang kotong su sonde parlú itu tukang jaga lai.<bt>So (consequently), those aforementioned religious regulations, are for example a babysitter/ child.minder who teaches us-inc well until Kristus come. But when He has already come, na, then we can believe Him, in order to live in a reciprocally good relationship with God. That's why now we-inc don't need that child.minder anymore. [Note to daughter translations: guardian needs to be more like an shepherd and guide and teacher than a bouncer. See Ex.Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paidagwgos: attendant, caretaker, guardian, custodian, guide,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">paidagwgos: attendant, caretaker, guardian, custodian, guide, superintendant, servant who took the children to and from school LITERALLY: So the Law was our caretaker to bring us to Christ, that we might be justified by faith.<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>LITERALLY: But faith has come, and we are no longer under a caretaker.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang parcaya su jadi Kristus pung kelu<bt>Believers have become Kristus' family</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sakarang bosong su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana, tagal bosong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>Now you-pl have become God's children, because you believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For you are all children"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For you are all children of God through faith in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Bosong samua yang su dapa sarani ko jadi Dia pung orang, ju ta'ika mati deng Dia.<bt>All of you-pl who have been baptised to become His people, are also completely bound/tied/linked with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enduw: to put on, to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">enduw: to put on, to be clothed, to become like LITERALLY: For as many of you as were baptized into Christ are clothed in him.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong samua su dapa sarani, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Bosong samua su dapa sarani, ko jadi Dia pung orang yang ta'ika mati deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Samua orang yang parcaya sang Kristus su sonde ada pung beda lai. Jadi biar bosong orang Yahudi ko, orang bukan Yahudi, budak ko bukan budak, laki-laki ko parampuan, samua orang yang ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus tu, sama.<bt>All people who believe in Kristus no longer have any differences. So whether you are Yahudi people, or, not Yahudi people, slaves or not slaves, male or female, all the people who are tied with Yesus Kristus, are the.same.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is not Jew or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is not Jew or Greek, neither slave or free man, neither male nor female, but you all are in [union with] Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Kristus tu, Abraham pung turunan yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu. Tagal bosong su ta'ika deng Kristus, andia ko bosong ju su jadi Abraham pung turunan yang batúl. Deng bagitu, bosong ju bisa tarima itu berkat yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang sang Abraham.<bt>The aforementioned Kristus, is Abraham descendant whom God pre-promised from long ago. Because you are tied/bound to Kristus, that's why you also have become Abraham's real/true descendants. In that manner/Because of that, you also can receive that blessing which God pre-promised to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleronomos: heir LITERALLY: If you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">kleronomos: heir LITERALLY: If you are of Christ, then you are Abraham's children, heirs according to the promise.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 4:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Beta kasi conto satu lai. Satu ana ada pung hak tarima pusaka dari dia pung bapa kalo dia pung bapa mati. Ma kalo dia pung umur balóm cukup, dia balóm bisa tarima itu pusaka, biar samua tu nanti jadi dia pung milik. Te kalo umur balóm cukup, dia tu sama ke budak yang sonde ada pung hak ko ame dia pung bos pung harta.<bt>I'll give another example. A child has the right to receive an inheritance from his/her father if/when his/her father dies. But if his/her age is not yet sufficient, s/he cannot yet receive that inheritance, even though it all will later become his/her possession. Cuz if age is not yet sufficient, he/she is the same as a slave who does not have the right to take his/her boss' belongings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diapherww: to differ kleronomos: heir|i(1) (1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">diapherww: to differ kleronomos: heir<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nepios: minor, child, not of age kurios: lord, owner<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: But I mean, as long as the heir is a child, he is no different from a slave, though he is owner of everything,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Tagal itu, musti ada orang yang urus sang dia deng dia pung pusaka. Itu ana musti iko itu tukang urus pung mau, sampe waktu yang dia pung bapa su putus, baru dia bole tarima ame dia pung pusaka.<bt>Because of that, there must be a person who watches.over him/her and his/her inheritance. That child must follow that child.minder's will, until the time which his/her father has decided, only then s/he may receive [+accomplishment] that inheritance of his/hers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitropos: guardian, a person to whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">epitropos: guardian, a person to whom the entire care of an underaged child is entrusted oikonomous: manager, trustee, administrator, steward<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>prothesmia: appointed time, set time LITERALLY: but he is under guardians and managers until the time set by his father.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Bagitu ju deng kotong. Waktu Yesus Kristus balóm datang, kotong masi sama ke itu ana kici. Te kotong masi ta'ika mati deng dunya pung cara pikir deng cara idop, sama ke satu budak.<bt>It's like that also with us-inc. When Yesus Kristus had not yet come, we-inc were still like that small child. Cuz we-inc were still completely tied/bound to the world's ways of thinking and ways of living, like a slave. [EXEG: Gk term is vague, and English translations split between 1) elemental principles, and 2) spiritual forces. Adding kuasa here would be good to capture the fuller range of meaning, but would be over translation, and set up a clash in later verses. Same Gk word is in vs.9 and needs lexical ties.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stoixeia: fundamental principles, basic principles, elementary"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">stoixeia: fundamental principles, basic principles, elementary principles, basic spirits kosmos: world, universe<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: So also we, when we were young, we were slaves under the [fundamental / basic] [elements / spirits] of the world;</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2013-04-18 01:25:44Z">.</Message></Annotation><v n="4-5" />Ma pas dia pung waktu, Tuhan Allah kirim datang Dia pung Ana yang jadi manusia, ko biar manusia ju bisa ta'angka jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana. Dia pung Ana tu, idop iko orang Yahudi pung atoran agama, ko biar Dia bisa kasi lapás samua orang yang dolu ada ta'ika deng itu atoran dong.<bt>But at the exact time, God sent His Child who became a human, so that humans also could be elevated/lifted/ adopted becoming God's2 children. That Child of His, lived according to the Yahudi people's religious regulations, so that He could free all people who were previously bound/tied to those aforementioned regulations. [EXEG: Gk here "redeemed", which works in KM /tabús ame/ for freeing s.o. from slavery.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if not clear, try “Ana kandung” in first sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when the right time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when the right time came, God sent forth his Son, made from woman, made under the Law, eksagorazw: to redeem<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>apolambanw: to receive huiothesia: adoption<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: to redeem those who were under the Law, that we might receive adoption as sons.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tagal bosong su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana dong, andia ko Dia su kirim datang Dia pung Ana pung Roh, ko maso pi dalam bosong pung hati. Deng bagitu, bosong ada pung hak pange sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa Bo'i&gt;&gt;.<bt>Because you-pl have become God's children, that's why He has sent His Child's Spirit to enter into your livers. In that manner/Because of that, you have the right to call God, &lt;&lt;Beloved Papa&gt;&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exapostellw: send out krazw: call, cry|i(6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">exapostellw: send out krazw: call, cry<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: Because you are sons, God sent the Spirit of his Son into our hearts, crying "Abba, Father".</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jadi sakarang bosong su bukan budak yang sonde ada pung hak tarima pusaka lai. Ma bosong su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana yang ada pung hak ko tarima samua pusaka yang Dia su janji.<bt>So now you-pl are no longer slaves who do not have the right to receive inheritance. But you have become God's child/ren who have the right to receive all that inheritance which His has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So that you are no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So that you are no longer a slave but a son. And since a son, also an heir through God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 8:15-17</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus jadi pikiran deng orang Galatia dong<bt>Paulus worries about the Galatia people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dolu, waktu bosong balóm kanál sang Tuhan Allah, bosong bekin diri jadi budak ko angka tinggi-tinggi deng iko hal-hal yang sonde batúl dong.<bt>Previously, when you-pl did not yet know God, you made yourselves become slave to elevate/highly value and follow/obey things were are not true. [NOTE: rev. Apr 2013]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pikiran deng = worry about, think"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">pikiran deng = worry about, think about (alot) [mesolectal!!]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phusis: nature LITERALLY: Formerly when you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">phusis: nature LITERALLY: Formerly when you did not know God, you were slaves to those who by nature are not gods;<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma sakarang bosong su kanál sang Tuhan Allah. Lebe bae kalo beta bilang kata, Tuhan Allah yang kanál sang bosong. Naa, karmana sampe bosong mau kambali lai, ko angka tinggi-tinggi deng iko ulang sang dunya pung cara pikir deng cara idop yang sonde ada pung guna, deng sonde ada pung kuasa apa-apa tu? Bosong mau bekin diri ta'ika deng itu hal dong, ko jadi dong pung budak lai, ko?<bt>But now you know God. It's better if I say that, it's God who knows you. Naa, how can it get to the point that you want to return again, to elevate/highly value and follow/obey again the world's ways of thinking and ways of living which have no use, and have no power? Do you want to make yourselves tied/bound with those things, to become their slaves again?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epistrephw: turn asthenes: sick, weak. Have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">epistrephw: turn asthenes: sick, weak. Have to change the order to put "not" at the end of the sentence so as to prevent its scope from including "junk"<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>ptwxos: begging poor, miserable stoixeia: elements, elementary principles, fundamental principles<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anwthen: again LITERALLY: But now knowing God, or rather, being known by God, why do you turn again to those weak and beggarly [elements / spirits] which want to enslave you again?<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Beta su dengar bilang, bosong ada kasi jalan atoran so'al agama pung hari-hari bae, iko dia pung hari, bulan, musim, deng taon, ko coba-coba mau bekin sanáng Tuhan Allah pung hati.<bt>I have heard that you are carrying out regulations about religious holidays following its days, months, seasons, and years, in order to try (reduplication implies: unsuccessfully) and make God's liver happy. [EXEG: ‘religiously’ implied by Gk word ‘observe (days)’ BAGD, GW, ES; although this could just as easily be adat as agama. Note the focus in the Gk here is on manner of observance (religiously), rather than law (religion, religious regs). But RL seems to have to make ‘religion’ explicit to capture the manner.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraterew: to keep LITERALLY: You observe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">paraterew: to keep LITERALLY: You observe days and months, and seasons, and years.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ini bekin beta jadi pikiran sa! Jang-jang beta pung cape ajar sang bosong sampe bagini lama ni, su jadi parcuma sa.<bt>This makes me worry! Lest my weariness/effort in teach you for this long, just becomes pointless.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jadi pikiran"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">jadi pikiran</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phobew: to fear mepws: lest somehow|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">phobew: to fear mepws: lest somehow<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>kopiaw: become tired LITERALLY: I fear for you, that somehow I have worked hard for you in vain.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta minta ko bosong idop bebas dari itu hal dong, sama ke beta ni. Te beta su idop talapás dari atoran agama sama ke bosong yang bukan Yahudi. Dolu waktu kotong ada sama-sama, beta sonde parná dapa susa dari bosong.<bt>Beloved siblings! I request that you live free of those things, like me here. Cuz (elaboration) I live free from religious regulations, the same as you who are non Yahudi. Previously when we-inc were together, I never received any trouble from you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deomai: to ask adikew: to do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">deomai: to ask adikew: to do wrong, to wrong someone<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: I beg you, brothers, be as I am, because I became like you. You have not done wrong to me;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Bosong samua tau bilang, tempo hari, waktu beta datang partama kali ko kasi tau itu Kabar Bae sang bosong, beta pung badan sonde kuat.<bt>You all know that, that prior time, when I came the first time to tell that Good News to you, may body was not strong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="astheneia: weakness, illness, sickness LITERALLY: You"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">astheneia: weakness, illness, sickness LITERALLY: You know that because of weakness/sickness of the flesh/body I preached to you the first time.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Biar bagitu, ma bosong sonde tola buang sang beta, tagal bosong tarima sang beta, sama ke beta ni, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga. Lebe-lebe lai, bosong tarima sang beta, sama ke beta ni, Yesus Kristus sandiri.<bt>Nevertheless, but you did not reject me, because you received me, just like I here, was God's underling from heaven. Even more, you received me, just like I here, was Yesus Kristus himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peirasmos: trial, test eksouthenew: despise, scorn,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">peirasmos: trial, test eksouthenew: despise, scorn, disdain someone<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>ekptuw: despise, disdain, reject, loath, spit out dexomai: receive, welcome<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: and even though my physical condition was a trial for you, you did not despise or reject me, but you received me as an angel of God, as Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Itu waktu, kotong sama-sama sanáng mau mati. Ma, akurang ko sakarang su sonde bagitu lai? Padahal itu waktu bosong sayang talalu sang beta, sampe-sampe bosong sadia do'i ame bosong pung mata biji sandiri ko kasi sang beta.<bt>At that time, we-inc all together were very happy. But, why is it no longer like that? In fact at that time you loved me very much, to.the point that you were prepared to gouge out your own eye/s to give to me. [“would have been willing to”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarismos: joy, happiness, blessing, satisfaction. NOT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">makarismos: joy, happiness, blessing, satisfaction. NOT "get plenny aloha fo me" marturew: bear witness, testify<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>exorussw: tear out, pluck out, pull out LITERALLY: Then where did your joy go? For I testify about you, that if possible, you would have plucked out your eyes and given them to me.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma sakarang bosong kira beta ni su jadi bosong pung musu, tagal beta omong yang batúl kasi sang bosong, ko?<bt>But now do you think I have become your enemy, because I speak that which true to you, [+tag question]?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aletheuw: be truthful exthros: the enemy|i(16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">aletheuw: be truthful exthros: the enemy<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: Have I now become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Itu tukang tipu dong sonde mau beta bakawan deng bosong, ais dong rajin babuju sang bosong, ko iko orang Yahudi pung atoran agama samua. Dong mau ko bosong batasibu ko iko-iko dong pung mau-mau sa.<bt>Those habitual decievers do not want me me to be friends with you, so they are diligent in persuading you to follow all the Yahudi people's religious regulations. They want for you to be busy-bodied following just their desires/wishes/ways. [EXEG: CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zelow: be zealous, be concerned for,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">zelow: be zealous, be concerned for, work hard for, to try to win someone's favor kalws: for good, for a good purpose<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>ekkleiw: exclude, shut out LITERALLY: They are zealous for you, but not for a good purpose. They desire to exclude you, that you may be zealous for them.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong pung maksud tu, memang sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Dong pung maksud tu, memang sonde bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma kalo bosong rajin bekin hal-hal yang bae, na, itu bae ju! Biar beta ada sama-sama deng bosong ko, sonde ko, bekin yang bae sa.<bt>But if you are diligent to do good things, na, that also good/ok! Regardless of whether I am together with you, or not, just do good (anyway).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is good to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is good to be zealous always, if the purpose is good, and not only when I am with you.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kalo dong rajin babuju sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Ma kalo dong rajin babuju sang bosong ko bekin hal-hal yang bae, na, itu bae ju!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ana sayang dong! Sakarang beta karjá karás lai kasi sang bosong, sampe beta su sama ke parampuan yang saki mau barana. Te beta sonde barenti karjá, sampe bosong pung hati su sama ke Kristus pung hati.<bt>Beloved children! Now I work had again for you, to the point that I am like a woman who in pain wanting to give birth. Cuz I do not stop working, until your livers have become the same as Kristus' liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wdinw: suffer birth pangs, experience childbirth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">wdinw: suffer birth pangs, experience childbirth pains mexri: until<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>morphow: to form LITERALLY: My little children, again I experience the pains of childbirth for you, until Christ is formed in you;<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma sakarang, beta su sonde tau mau bekin apa deng bosong lai! Beta su rindu mau pi ba'omong langsung deng bosong, ko biar beta sonde usa omong karás bagini.<bt>But now, I no longer know what to do with you! I long to go speak directly with you, so that I don't need to speak harshly like this.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: to wish pareimi: to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">thelw: to wish pareimi: to be present<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>allassw: change phwne: voice, sound, tone<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>aporew: be uncertain, doubt, be perplexed, be unsure LITERALLY: I wish to be present with you now, and change my tone, because I am uncertain about you.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kasi umpama pake carita so'al Hagar pung ana, deng Sara pung ana<bt>Paulus gives an example using the story about Hagar's child, and Sara's child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Kalo bosong mau idop iko orang Yahudi pung atoran agama, na, lebe bae bosong mangarti dolu itu atoran pung maksud.<bt>If you-pl want to live according to the Yahudi people's religious regulations, na, it's best if you first understand the intent of those regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tell me, you who desire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tell me, you who desire to be under the Law, do you not hear the Law?</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada carita so'al dong pung ba'i Abraham pung ana laki-laki dua orang. Dia dapa ana satu dari dia pung budak, deng yang satu lai dari dia pung bini sah, yang bukan budak.<bt>Cuz in God2's Holy Writing there is a story about their Gf/Ff Abraham's two male children. He got one child from his slave, and the other one from his legal wife, who was not a slave. [DISCOURSE referent tracking: Gk uses slave and free, names Hagar and Sara, flesh and promise. Local mechanisms track using names Hagar and Sara, slave and wife. (Slave and free falls flat, is hard to phrase, and communicates nothing.) Don't force it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added last clause to track"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** added last clause to track “free”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paidiske: maid, female servant eleutheros: free|i(22)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">paidiske: maid, female servant eleutheros: free<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: For it has been written that Abraham had two sons, one from the female slave and one from the free woman.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 16:15, 21:2</note><v n="23" />Budak tu, barana ame dia pung ana, tagal iko manusia pung mau-mau. Ma bini sah tu, barana ame dia pung ana, tagal Tuhan Allah su janji memang bagitu kasi sang Abraham.<bt>That slave, gave birth to her child, because of following human desires. But that wife, gave birth to her child, because God had already pre-promised like that to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the one from the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the one from the slave woman was born according to the flesh, but the one from the free woman through promise.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Itu parampuan dua tu, jadi umpama ko kasi tunju dua janji yang Tuhan Allah bekin deng manusia. Janji yang satu, Dia bekin deng ba'i Musa di gunung Sinai, waktu Dia kasi turun orang Yahudi pung atoran agama dong. Orang yang ta'ika deng itu atoran agama, dong ju budak sama ke Hagar.<bt>Those two aforementioned women, become an example to show two promises which God made with humans. The one promise He made with Gf/Ff Musa at Sinai mountain, when He sent down the Yahudi people's religious regulations. People who are tied/bound to those religious regulations, they are also slaves the same as Hagar.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="allegorew: to speak allegorically, to tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">allegorew: to speak allegorically, to tell a parable, to speak figuratively diatheke: covenant, agreement, will and testament<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>douleia: slavery LITERALLY: Which, to speak allegorically, the women represent two agreements. One is from Mt. Sinai, giving birth to slavery, which is Hagar.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Itu tampa di gunung Sinai di tana Arab, sama ke Hagar ju. Samua orang Yerusalem sakarang yang masi ta'ika deng itu atoran agama Yahudi, dong budak sama ke Hagar ju.<bt>That place on Sinai mountain in that Arab land, is also like Hagar. All the Yerusalem people now who are still tied to those Yahudi religious regulations, they also are slaves like Hagar.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sustoixew: to correspond to LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">sustoixew: to correspond to LITERALLY: For Hagar is Mt. Sinai in Arabia, corresponding to present-day Jerusalem, and is in slavery with her children.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ma janji yang laen tu, kasi tunju satu kota Yerusalem yang laen di sorga. Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana yang tenga di situ, bukan budak. Te dong tu, orang bebas yang sonde ta'ika deng itu atoran agama dong. Andia ko dong sama ke botong pung mama Sara, andia Abraham pung bini sah.<bt>But that other promise, shows/designates another Yerusalem city in heaven. God's children who live there, are not slaves. Cuz they, are free people who are not tied to those religious regulations. That's why they are like our-ex mama Sara, that wife of Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the Jerusalem from above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the Jerusalem from above is free, which is our mother;</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Te dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang:<bt>Cuz in God's Holy Writing it is written, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Woi! Parampuan yang sonde bisa barana!<bt>&lt;&lt;Woi! [+challenge] Woman who cannot give birth!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin sanáng lu pung hati su!<bt>Make your liver happy!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Woi! Parampuan yang sonde rasa saki barana!<bt>Woi! [+challenge] Woman who has not felt pain bearing children!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Manyanyi sanáng-sanáng su!<bt>Sing happily!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Parampuan yang hati ancor, tagal dia pung laki su sonde toe sang dia lai,<bt>The woman whose liver is destroyed because her husband no longer pays attention to her anymore,</bt><note reference="4:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Parampuan yang hati ancor tagal dia pung laki su sonde toe sang dia lai tu, andia Sara. Te Abraham pi ame sang Hagar ko dapa ana.<bt>That woman whose liver was destroyed because her husband no longer paid attention to her, that is Sara. Cuz Abraham went and took Hagar in order to get a child.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dia dapa ana lebe banya dari parampuan yang dapa laki.&gt;&gt;<bt>later she will get more children than the woman who has a/the husband.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: people easily interpret who is who here incorrectly. EXEG: Gk. /eremos/ abandoned, desolate, deserted (by someone), forsaken, barren (has both an emotional aspect as well as a factual aspect); Fung, Bruce, TN, and TH all associate “the desolate woman” with Sara, and “the one with the husband” as Hagar.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euphraivw: to be glad, to rejoice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">euphraivw: to be glad, to rejoice steira: barren<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>tiktw: to give birth hregnumi: to tear, break loose, break out<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>boaw: to shout wdinw: to suffer the pains of childbirth<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>eremos: desolate, barren LITERALLY: For it has been written, "Rejoice, barren one who has not given birth, break loose and shout, one who has not had childbirth pains, because many more are the children of the deserted one, than of her who has a husband."<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 54:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jadi sodara dong! Dolu Tuhan Allah janji ko kasi ana sang Abraham. Ma lama-lama baru Tuhan bekin iko Dia pung janji, ko bekin Sara barana Isak kasi Abraham. Kotong ju sama ke Isak, tagal Tuhan Allah janji kasi turunan laen sang Abraham ju.<bt>So (consequently) siblings! Previously God promised to give a child to Abraham. But it was a long time before God2 fulfilled His promise, to make Sara give birth to Isak for Abraham. We-inc are also like Isak, because God also promised to give other descendants to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you brothers, you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you brothers, you are children of promise like Isaac.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Waktu itu ana budak yang lahir iko manusia pung mau tu, su bésar datang, dia bekin sangsara sang Isak yang lahir iko Tuhan pung Roh pung mau. Itu ju sama ke apa yang jadi sakarang.<bt>When that slave child who was born according to human will, was grown up, he tormented Isak who was born according to God's Spirit's will. That also is like what happens now.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: At that time the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: At that time the one who was born according to the flesh persecuted the one [born] according to the Spirit, thus it is now.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 21:9</note><v n="30" />Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Usir buang itu budak deng dia pung ana. Te budak pung ana sonde ada pung hak tarima pusaka. Cuma bini sah pung ana sa yang ada pung hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>God2's Holy Writing writes saying, &lt;&lt;Expel/throw out that slave and her child. Cuz the slave child does not have the right to receive inheritance. Only just the wife's child who has the right.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk has /alla/ ‘but’ conjunction here, however, none of the KM conjunctions makes sense, so we have left it denuded like the CEV, rather than imply a connection that is forced.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But what does the Scripture"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But what does the Scripture say? "Throw out the slave woman and her son, for the son of the slave woman will not inherit with the son of the free woman."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 21:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Kotong ni bukan sama ke budak pung ana, tagal kotong su sonde ta'ika lai deng orang Yahudi pung atoran agama. Te kotong ni, sama ke ana dari Abraham pung bini sah, tagal kotong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>So it's like this, siblings! We-inc here are not like the slave's child, because we-inc are no longer tied/bound anymore with the Yahudi people's religious regulations. Cuz (elaboration) we here are like the child from Abraham's legal wife, because we believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, we are not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, we are not children of the slave women, but of the free woman.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus su kasi bebas sang kotong<bt>Kristus has freed us</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Dolu orang Yahudi pikol barát-barát dong pung atoran agama dong. Ma sakarang Kristus su angka itu barát dari orang yang parcaya sang Dia. Andia ko, sakarang kotong su bebas. Jadi bosong jang kaná tipu ko pi pikol ulang lai itu atoran, sama ke budak!<bt>Previously the Yahudi people heavily-heavily shoulder carried their religious regulations. But now Kristus has lifted that heaviness from people who believe in Him. That's why, now we-inc are free. So (consequently) don't you-pl be decieved into shoulder carrying those regulations again, like a slave.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Dengar, é! Ini beta, Paulus, yang omong ni. Kalo bosong tarima sunat ko iko orang Yahudi dong pung atoran, na, Kristus pung mati yang bekin bosong jadi bebas, sonde ada pung guna lai.<bt>Listen! This is me, Paulus, who is speaking here. If you accept circumcision in order to follow the Yahudi people's regulations, na, that death of Kristus which made you free, no longer has any value/worth.</bt><v n="3" />Kalo orang tarima sunat, dia ju musti pikol ulang lai itu atoran dong samua. Bosong inga, ko sonde? Te dolu, beta su kasi tau memang.<bt>If a person accept circumcision, s/he also must shoulder carry again all those regulations. Do you remember that, or not? Cuz previously, I have already told you that.</bt><v n="4" />Orang yang mau pake atoran ko bekin Tuhan Allah tarima bae sang dia, dia bekin diri tapisa dari Kristus. Te deng bagitu, dia su tola buang Tuhan Allah pung hati bae.<bt>A person who uses regulations to make God accept him/her, s/he makes him/herself separated from Kristus. Cuz by doing that, s/he has rejected God's good liver (*mercy).</bt><v n="5" />Ma Tuhan pung Roh Barisi yang buka jalan ko kotong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Andia ko kotong batunggu-tunggu bilang, nanti Tuhan Allah cap sang kotong bilang, kotong orang hati lurus.<bt>But God's HS is the one who opens the way for us-inc to believe in YK. That is why we keep waiting eagerly that later God will cap/brand us as straight/righteous people. [EXEG: Bruce]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Changed exeg *** (whole verse)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Changed exeg *** (whole verse)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta omong bagitu, tagal beta parcaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Beta omong bagitu, tagal beta parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Allah pung Roh. Te Dia su kasi tau memang bilang, Tuhan tantu tarima bae orang yang parcaya sang Kristus.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Biar orang sunat ko, sonde ko, itu sonde pantíng. Ma yang pantíng, andia orang parcaya sang Kristus, deng sayang sang orang laen ju.<bt>Whether a person is circumcised or not or [whatever], that is not important. But what is important is that people believe in Kristus, and (consequently) love other people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dolu bosong su idop iko jalan yang batúl. Ma sakarang sapa yang su putar-balek sang bosong, sampe bosong su sonde iko itu jalan lai?<bt>Previously you-pl lived following the path that is true. But now who is it that has decieved you, to the point that you don't follow that path anymore?</bt><v n="8" />Te ajaran putar-balek yang bosong dengar tu, sonde datang dari Tuhan Allah. Padahal Dia tu, yang su pange ame sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung orang.<bt>Cuz (flagging explication) that deceptive teaching which you have heard, doesn't come from God. Whereas in fact it's God, who called you-pl to become His people.</bt><v n="9" />Apa yang dong ajar, mula-mula cuma satu-dua kata sa. Ma lama-lama nanti itu ajaran su bekin bosong pung pikiran jadi rusak. Sama ke ragi sadiki yang orang campor deng tarigu ko mau bekin roti. Lama-lama ju, itu ragi bekin camporan jadi reis samua.<bt>That which they teach, orginally was just one or two words. [CHECK UNS suggestion /mula-mula cuma/ &gt; more mesolectal /partama cuma/] But eventually that teaching has made destroyed your thinking. Just like a little bit of yeast which a person mixed with flour to make bread. Eventually that yeast makes all the dough raise.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="camporan roti = dough, adonan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">camporan roti = dough, adonan</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 5:6</note><v n="10" />Tagal kotong su jadi satu deng kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, andia ko beta yakin bilang, Dia nanti bekin bosong parcaya kambali deng apa yang beta su ajar. Deng Tuhan Allah sandiri nanti hukum sapa sa yang su bekin rusak bosong pung parcaya.<bt>Because we-inc have become one/united with our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus, that's why I am certain that, He will make you-pl believe again in that teaching which I taught. And God himself will judge/punish whoever it is who has destroyed your faith. [EXEG: TH, BIS]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Bagini, sodara dong! Kalo beta ajar bilang, orang musti dapa sunat, na, tantu beta sonde dapa siksa lai sama ke sakarang ni. Deng orang Yahudi dong sonde tola buang beta pung ajaran lai so'al Yesus pung mati di kayu palang.<bt>It's like this siblings! If I teach that people must be circumcised, na, surely I won't be mistreated/abused anymore like I am now. And the Yahudi people won't reject anymore my teaching about Yesus' death on that cross.</bt><v n="12" />Ma itu orang yang su bekin bingung sang bosong so'al sunat tu, kasi tenga pi ko dong sandiri pi potong buang dong pung &lt;burung&gt; samua!<bt>But those people who have confused you about circumcision, let them go and cut off their own entire 'bird' (euphemism for male genitals)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Sodara dong! Tuhan su kasi bebas sang bosong, ko bosong sonde usa idop ta'ika deng itu atoran agama pung mau. Ma jang kira kata, bosong su bebas ko idop iko bosong pung mau-mau! Te yang batúl, andia bosong musti idop basayang, deng bosong musti layani satu deng satu, sama ke budak layani dia pung tuan.<bt>Siblings! God2 has freed you-pl, so that you don't need to live bound to the way of those religious regulations. But don't think that, you are free to live according to your own will! Cuz what's true, is that you must live loving each other, and you must serve/take.care.of each other, like a slave serves/takes.care.of his master.</bt><v n="14" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu musti sayang orang laen dong, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt; Kalo bosong cuma bekin iko ini atoran satu sa, na, bosong su bekin iko orang Yahudi pung atoran pung maksud samua.<bt>In God's Holy Writing it is written saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg must love other people, the same as you love your own self.&gt;&gt; If you-pl only follow just this one regulation, na, you-pl have followed the intent of all the Yahudi people's regulations.</bt><note reference="5:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note><v n="15" />Ma kalo bosong satu bara'u deng satu, ko satu baru'i deng satu, na, lia sa! Sonde lama lai, te bosong su kasi ancor bosong pung diri sandiri.<bt>But if you argue/be.at.odds with each other, so that you are yanking/pulling (fighting words) each other, just watch out. No much longer, and you-pl will have destroyed yourselves.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Idop iko manusia pung mau, ko, iko Roh Barisi pung mau?<bt>Live according to the will of humans, or according to the will of the Holy Spirit?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta pung maksud bagini: kalo bosong idop iko Tuhan pung Roh pung mau, bosong sonde iko manusia pung mau lai.<bt>My intent is like this: if you live according to will of God's Spirit, you-pl don't follow the will of human/s anymore. [EXEG: NLT, CEV] [NOTE to daughter translations (ALT): could be phrased in the imperative.]</bt><v n="17" />Te manusia pung mau sonde iko Roh pung mau. Deng Roh pung mau sonde iko manusia pung mau. Ko dong dua bamalawan na! Andia ko bosong sonde bole bekin lai, iko bosong pung mau-mau sa.<bt>Cuz the will of human/s does not follow the will of the Spirit, and the will of the Spirit does not follow the will of human/s. Cuz obviously the two are in opposition! That's why you-pl may no long act, just according to your-pl own wills. [EXEG: TN]</bt><note reference="5:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 7:15-23</note><v n="18" />Ma kalo Tuhan pung Roh ada pimpin sang bosong, bosong su sonde ta'ika lai deng itu atoran dong.<bt>But if God's Spirit is leading you-pl, you are no longer tied/bound to those regulations.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Orang yang bekin-bekin iko manusia pung mau tu, conto ke: orang yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dia pung laki ko dia pung bini, orang yang pung pikiran kotor, yang sonde tau malu,<bt>Those people who act in a manner that follows the will of humans, are for example: people who sexually play.around with a person who is not his/her husband or his/her wife, people who have dirty thinking, who have no shame,</bt><v n="20" />yang songgo setan ko suanggi, yang bamusu, yang suka basambung mulu, yang suka ba'iri hati, yang suka mangamok, yang cuma inga diri sandiri, yang suka tusu-tusu orang, yang suka bekin kaco,<bt>who traditional.worship evil spirits or sorcery, who are enemies with each other, who habitually quarrel/squabble, who habitually have jealous livers, who habitually run amuck/get.violently.angry, who only think of themselves, who habitually poke/incite other people, who habitually make chaos,</bt><v n="21" />yang suka camburu, yang suka minum mabo, yang bapesta liar, deng yang bekin sala laen dong. Dolu beta su parná kasi inga bilang, orang yang bekin iko hal-hal bagitu, dong tu sonde bisa jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.<bt>who habitually are envious, who habitually drink [until] drunk, those who have wild parties (UNS's give back: partying that may involve heavy drinking, drugs, and sex), and who do other wrongs. Previously I have reminded you that, people who do things like that, they cannot become God's people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bapesta gila-gila = bapesta liar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">bapesta gila-gila = bapesta liar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma orang yang idop iko Tuhan pung Roh pung mau, nanti itu Roh bekin dia ko jadi orang yang suka basayang, yang pung hati babunga, yang suka badame, yang sabar, yang pung hati bae deng orang, yang suka batolong orang, yang suka bapegang janji,<bt>But a person who lives according the will of God's Spirit, that Spirit will make him/her become a person who habitually loves, whose liver is flowered (=joyful person), who habitually lives in peaceful relationships, who is patient, who has a good liver toward other people (=generous, kindhearted, merciful); who habitually helps other people, who habitually holds.on.to/fulfills his/her promises, [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk has two senses ‘generous’ and ‘goodness’ (NLT, CEV, LN), check that your term includes the ‘generous’ sense. NRSV]</bt><v n="23" />yang manis deng samua orang, deng yang bisa jaga diri bae-bae. Sonde ada satu atoran ju, yang larang ini hal dong.<bt>who is sweet (=kind, polite) to all people, and who can control him/herself well. There is not a single regulation, which forbids these things. [NOTE to daughter translations: check that “jaga diri” isn't too broad.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="praytees: gentleness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">praytees: gentleness</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Orang yang su maso jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang, dia su sonde iko manusia pung mau lai. Te itu kapingin bekin jahat dong su tapaku mati di kayu palang sama-sama deng Yesus.<bt>A person who has entered to become Yesus Kristus' person, s/he is no longer tied anymore to the will of human/s. Cuz those desires to do evil have been nailed dead (=totally nailed down) on the cross together with Yesus.</bt><v n="25" />Jadi kalo Tuhan pung Roh su kasi idop baru sang kotong, na, kotong musti bekin iko tarús Dia pung mau.<bt>So (consequently), if God's Spirit has given new life to us-inc, na, we-inc must continually follow His will.</bt><v n="26" />Andia ko kotong jang bagila hormat, jang suka bamalawan satu deng satu, deng jang ba'iri hati lai.<bt>That's why we-inc we no longer crazily seek respect (=wanting others to defer to us, putting ourselves up), [we] don't habitually oppose each other, and [we] aren't jealous anymore. [NOTE to daughter translations: @@</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="REVISE EXEG @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">REVISE EXEG @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Batolong satu deng satu<bt>Helping each other</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara dong! Kalo orang parcaya satu ada bekin sala, na, bosong yang kanál batúl Tuhan pung Roh pung mau, pi omong deng dia pake hati manis. Ais bawa kambali sang dia, ko dia iko Tuhan pung jalan yang batúl. Ma jaga bosong pung diri ko jang jato iko dia pung sala.<bt>Siblings! If a believer does wrong, na, you-pl who truly know (personal knowledge, not head knowledge) God's Spirit's will/ways, go speak with him/her using a sweet liver (=a nice approach). Then bring him/her back, so that s/he follows God2's path which is true. But watch yourselves lest you fall by following that wrong of his/hers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katartizw: restore, put in order, restore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">katartizw: restore, put in order, restore to former condition, make right, correct in order to restore paraptwma: trespass, transgression, false step, offense<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>peirazw: tempt, try, test, enticement to sin pneumatikos: spiritual, living by the Spirit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>prautes: humility, meekness, gentleness, the opposite of arrogance or harshness prolambanw: overtake, detect, surprise someone<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>skopew: notice, consider, paying attention, be careful LITERALLY: Brothers, if a person is detected in some sin, you who are spiritual, restore the person in a spirit of gentleness, paying attention to yourself, so that you will not be tempted.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kalo orang dapa susa, na, bosong yang laen bantu sang dia. Te deng bagitu bosong bekin iko Kristus pung atoran.<bt>If a person gets trouble/difficulty, na, you-pl others help him/her. Cuz by doing that you act according to Kristus' regulation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anaplerow make complete, fulfill, satisfy the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anaplerow make complete, fulfill, satisfy the requirements of baros: weight, burden, load, heavy load<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>bastaxw: carry, bear LITERALLY: Bear each others' burdens, an so fulfill the law of Christ.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kalo ada orang yang angka-angka diri bilang, dia lebe dari orang laen, padahal sonde bagitu, na, dia su tipu ame dia pung diri sandiri.<bt>If a person lifts him/herself up saying s/he is more/better than other people, when in actual fact it's not like that, na, that means s/he is decieving him/herself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phrenapataw: to deceive LITERALLY: For if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">phrenapataw: to deceive LITERALLY: For if a person thinks he is something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Jadi tiap orang musti pareksa apa yang dia bekin. Kalo apa yang dia bekin tu, su bae, nanti dia puas sandiri. Jang banding-banding deng orang laen.<bt>So (consequently) each person must examine that which s/he does. If that which s/he does, is good, then s/he can be satisfied of him/herself. Don't compare around with other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimazw: examine, test kauxema: boast|i(4) (4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">dokimazw: examine, test kauxema: boast<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: But let each person examine his own actions, and then he will have reason to boast because of himself alone, and not because of another.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Beta omong bagitu, tagal tiap orang musti tanggong sandiri apa yang dia bekin.<bt>I speak like that, because each person must be responsible him/her self for that which s/he does.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phortion: load, normal duty LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">phortion: load, normal duty LITERALLY: For each person should carry his own load.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma orang yang tarima Tuhan pung ajaran, dia musti bagi dia pung karjá pung hasil, ko bantu orang yang ajar sang dia.<bt>But a person who accepts God2's teaching, s/he must divide the results of his/her work, to help that person who has taught him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koinwnew: share, give someone a share"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">koinwnew: share, give someone a share of something, give material things, participate katexew: teach<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: But let the one who is being taught the word share every good thing with the one who teaches.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Inga, é! Tuhan Allah tau samua. Jadi jang tipu bosong pung diri sandiri, deng jang coba-coba tipu sang Dia. Te apa yang orang tanam di kabón, nanti dia dapa kambali dia pung hasil.<bt>Remember! God knows everything. So (consequently), don't decieve yourselves, and don't try to decieve Him. Cuz that which a person plants in a garden, later he will get back that harvest/result.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="therizw: reap, harvest mukterizw: treat with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">therizw: reap, harvest mukterizw: treat with contempt, mock, make a fool of<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>planaw: deceive, be mistaken speirw: sow, plant<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Do not be deceived, God is not mocked. Whatever a person plants, that he will harvest.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Bagitu ju, kalo orang bekin hal jahat iko dia pung mau, nanti dia dapa kambali idop yang ancor. Ma kalo orang bekin hal bae iko Roh Barisi pung mau, nanti itu orang dapa kambali idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>It's like that also, if a person does evil things according to his/her will, later s/he will get back a destroyed life. But if a person does good things according to the Holy Spirit's will, later that person will get back true life which does not stop. [EXEG: Bruce, on "corruption" = "indulgence in such things would have disastrous results in their personal and corporate lives alike."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tweaked exeg of corruption and phrasing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">***tweaked exeg of corruption and phrasing of eternal life</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="therizw reap, harvest phthora: ruin|i(8) (8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">therizw reap, harvest phthora: ruin<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>speirw: sow, plant LITERALLY: Because he who plants for the sinful nature harvests destruction from the sinful nature, but he who plants for the Spirit, from the Spirit harvests eternal life.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu ju kalo orang bekin hal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Bagitu ju kalo orang bekin hal jahat iko dia pung mau, nanti dia dapa kambali sangsara di api naraka. Ma kalo orang bekin hal bae iko Roh Barisi pung mau, nanti dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan di sorga.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Tagal itu, bosong jang malas bekin hal-hal bae. Te pas dia pung waktu, kotong ju dapa kambali hasil yang bae, asal kotong batahan tarús.<bt>Because of that, you-pl should get lazy/disinterested in doing good things. Cuz at the right time, we-inc will also get back good results/harvest, as long as we-inc continually endure.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egkakew: become weary, get tired ekluw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">egkakew: become weary, get tired ekluw: become weary, get slack, give up, become discouraged<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: Let us not get tired in doing good, because in due time we will reap/receive if we do not give up.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi kalo kotong ada sampát, na, kotong bekin hal bae memang kasi samua orang, lebe-lebe kasi kotong pung sodara orang parcaya dong.<bt>So (consequently) if/when we-inc have opportunity, na, we should go ahead and do good things for all people, and especially for our believing siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, as often as we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, as often as we have the chance, let us do good to everyone, but especially to the family of believers.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus tutu dia pung surat<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sakarang beta sandiri yang tulis ini surat, pake huruf bésar-bésar.<bt>Now it's I myself who are writing this letter, using big-big letters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Look what big letters I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Look what big letters I write with my own hand!</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Inga, é! Itu tukang tipu dong ju parcaya sang Yesus Kristus yang mati di kayu palang. Ma dong mau paksa sang bosong ko tarima sunat, tagal dong taku orang Yahudi yang laen nanti siksa sang dong, kalo dong ajar bilang, Tuhan Allah ju tarima bae orang yang sonde iko atoran sunat. Andia ko dong cari-cari muka di itu orang Yahudi dong.<bt>Remember! Those habitual decievers also believe in Yesus Kristus who died on the cross. But they want to force you-pl to accept circumcision, because they are afraid other Yahudi people will mistreat them, if they teach that, God also accepts people who do not follow the circumcision regulation. That's why they are trying to find face (=trying to please; 'suck up to') those Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anagkazw: compel, make, force diwkw: persecute|i(12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">anagkazw: compel, make, force diwkw: persecute<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>euproswpew: make a good showing, make a good impression LITERALLY: Those who want to make a good impression outwardly are trying to make you be circumcised. The only reason they do this is to avoid being persecuted for the cross of Christ.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma biar dong su sunat ju, dong sandiri sonde iko atoran agama samua. Dong mau ko bosong tarima sunat ko jadi dong pung orang. Deng bagitu, dong pung partei angka-angka sang dong.<bt>But even though they are circumcised, they don't follow all the religious regulations themselves. They want you-pl to accept circumcision to become their people. By that, their party (=faction/group) will praise them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Not even those who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Not even those who are circumcised obey the law, but they want you to be circumcised that they may boast about your flesh.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma kalo beta ni, beta cuma mau angka-angka sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus. Dia mati di kayu palang, ko kasi mati hal-hal jahat yang manusia bekin, iko dunya pung mau. Andia ko beta su sonde ame pusing lai deng dunya pung mau. Deng dunya pung mau sonde ika lai sang beta.<bt>But as for me here, I only want to praise our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus. He died on the cross, to kill the evil things which humans do in following the world's will. That's why I am no longer concerned (=don't pay attention to, respond to) anymore about the world's will. And the things/desires/cares of this world do not bind me anymore. [EXEG: Careful not to fall into the trap of a cute saying, making Paul out to being a lying shyster saying something that is blatantly not true, As CEV “the world is dead as far as I am concerned, and I am dead as far as the world is concerned.” Or NLT “my interest in this world died long ago, and the world's interest in me is also long dead.” According to Acts and Paul's epistles, kings, emporors, governors, centurions, priests, religions, rivals, underlings, and dozens of Christian congregations scattered around the known world were consumed with interest in Paul's welfare (usually polarised pro or con).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added last sentence to complete"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** added last sentence to complete the cute saying</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But may it never be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But may it never be that I should ever boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Sunat ko, sonde sunat ko, itu sonde pantíng. Ma yang pantíng, andia kotong tarima idop baru dari Tuhan.<bt>Circumcision or, not circumcision or [whatever], that's not important. But what is important, is that we-inc receive new life from God2. [NOTE to daughter translations: Don't artificially force trying to keep the “creation” word here, which would skew the focus away from a transformed life theme of Galatians and onto the Genesis story. NLT, CEV “new person”; HCE “make new inside”; TN “The word translated creation is the same word Paul uses in 2 Corinthians 5:17 concerning a person becoming a new creation when he is born again. Some may prefer to say: “what is important is that a person has found new life.”; Fung “here is not the act of creation as in Rom. 1:20, but the result of the creative act.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akrobustia: uncircumcised LITERALLY: For circumcision is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">akrobustia: uncircumcised LITERALLY: For circumcision is not anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Beta minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung sayang sang samua orang yang iko beta pung ajaran ni, ko dong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng, ju kasi tunju rasa kasian satu deng satu. Te dong su jadi Tuhan Allah pung bangsa yang baru.<bt>I request that God shows His love to all people who follow this teaching of mine, so that they may live in mutually peaceful relationships, and show mercy/pity to each other. Cuz they have become God's new nation. [Follows NLT] [EXEG: Gk /eleos/ ‘mercy, pity’ here. The concept of ‘mercy’ is often problematic for us. Our words in this region for ‘love’ tend to be something like 80% ‘love’ and 20% ‘mercy, pity’. So ‘love’ here in the first clause, combined with ‘mercy/pity’ in the last clause gets the same end result.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added mercy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** added mercy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eirene: peace eleos: mercy, pity|i(16) (16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">eirene: peace eleos: mercy, pity<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>kanwn: rule stoixew: be in line with, follow this rule, live by this principle<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: As many as live according to this rule, peace to them and mercy, and upon the Israel of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jujur sa, beta su sonde mau ko orang maen ganggu sang beta deng ini parkara lai. Te beta pung badan su ada bakás luka, tagal beta layani sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>To be honest, I don't want anyone to keep bothering/distracting me any more over this matter. Cuz my body already has the remains of wounds (=scars), because I serve Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** OV 2nd sentence &quot;addition&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">*** OV 2nd sentence "addition"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Finally, let no man trouble"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Finally, let no man trouble me, for I carry on my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jujur sa, beta su sonde mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z">Jujur sa, beta su sonde mau ame pusing deng ini parkara lai. Yang pantíng, Yesus su kasi hak sang beta ko ajar Dia pung Kabar Bae. Deng beta pung badan su ada bakás luka, tagal beta layani sang Dia.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Sodara dong! Beta minta ko kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong samua.<bt>Siblings! I request that our-inc Bos Yesus Kristus show His good liver (*mercy) to all of you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The grace of our Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:50:39Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirits, brothers. Amen!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bagitu sa!<bt>That's it!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Salam dari beta,<bt>Greetings from me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>